==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monitory
<hw>Mon"i*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>monitorius</ets>.]</ety> <def>Giving admonition; instructing by way
of caution; warning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Losses, miscarriages, and disappointments, are <qex>monitory</qex>
and instructive.</q> <rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monitory</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Monitory
<hw>Mon"i*to*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Admonition; warning;
especially, a monition proceeding from an ecclesiastical court, but not
addressed to any one person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monitrix</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Monitress</ent>⟦br⟧
